    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nPR #6531 introduces CLI argument for generating shared module. The workflow using new argument does not integrate well into setuptools machinery because it needs one extra step of calling cython.\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nWe should integrate generating shared module in `cythonize()` to generate shared utility extention module together with compilation of cython files. Hence, for following code structure:\n\n```\nmypkg/\n+-- __init__.py\n+-- subpkg1/\n    +-- __init__.py\n    +-- module.pyx\n```\n\nwe should be able to write following `setup.py` file:\n\n```python\nfrom Cython.Build import cythonize\nfrom setuptools import setup, Extension\n\nextensions = [\n    Extension(\"*\", [\"**/*.pyx\"]),\n]\n\nsetup(\n  ext_modules = cythonize(extensions, shared_utility_qualified_name='mypkg.shared._cyutility')\n)\n```\n\nbuild system will produce following structure:\n\n```\nmypkg/\n+-- __init__.py\n+-- shared/\n|   +-- __init__.py\n|   +-- _cyutility.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so  \n+-- subpkg1/\n    +-- __init__.py\n    +-- module.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so\n```\n\nwhere:\n1. `_cyutility.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so` is shared utility extension module automatically generated and compiled by the build system.\n2. `module.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so` is compiled with `shared_utility_qualified_name` directive set to `mypkg.shared._cyutility`\n3. build system will create all necessary directories and `__init__.py` files if they do not exists to ensure that shared utility is importable under provided full qualified module name.\n4. build system will automatically compile all extensions passed to `cythonize()` with proper directive to use utility code from shared utility extention module. \n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\nN/A\n\n### Additional context\n\nSee discussion in https://mail.python.org/pipermail/cython-devel/2025-February/005466.html",
